The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ispat back in the black

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 6: Ispat Industries Limited has posted a profit after tax of Rs 82.12 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2007. It suffered a loss of Rs 153.14 crore in the corresponding period a year ago. The companys bottomline improved by Rs 235 crore because of higher production and sales and shift to a value-added product mix.

 Ispats total income for the quarter rose 64.6 per cent to Rs 2,141.58 crore.

 The profit before tax increased to Rs 359.48 crore during the fourth quarter from Rs 225.44 crore in the year-ago period.

 Ispat posted a profit before tax of Rs 3.37 crore for the financial year 2006-07 compared with a loss of Rs 1,196.85 crore in the previous fiscal.

 Ispats total income increased 52 per cent to Rs 7,595.49 crore in 2006-07 from Rs 5,010.73 crore in 2005-06.

 Ispat has brought down its loss to Rs 9.53 crore in 2006-07 from Rs 812.67 crore in 2005-06. This was after paying a deferred tax charge of Rs 9.87 crore for 2006-07. 




